<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="979" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d979">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17552.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Ambassador of Argentina</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I received your letter
                            of yesterday informing me [etc.]</p>
                        <p>I think you are right that the time agreed upon for receiving answers
                            from Mexico will expire within a very few days, but at the same time I
                            feel that Carranza should be given every opportunity <pb facs="0862" n="746" xml:id="pg_746"/> to reply to our communication in order
                            that he may have no excuse that we acted hastily.</p>
                        <p>I believe that we shall receive his answer in a very few days, although
                            it may be delayed possibly until the end of this week. As soon as I can
                            state anything positively I will communicate with you at once.</p>
                        <p>With warm regard [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>